                  <summary>1 copy of Mufarriḥ al-qulūb by Tāj al-Dīn ibn Muʿīn al-Dīn Malikī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85121918 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100087" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_948A-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar ur">Persian, Arabic, Urdu</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_151">Mufarriḥ al-qulūb</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_151">مفرّح القلوب</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Persian translation by the <persName key="viaf_317199908" role="aut">Muftī al-Mulk Tāj al-Dīn ibn Muʿīn al-Dīn Malikī</persName> of the Sanskrit book of four fables entitled <title key="work_151">Hitopadesa</title> by <persName key="viaf_50552807" role="ant">Nārāyan</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 109v): written for the consultation of Bhīm Singh, 25 Jumādá al-Avval 1182/7 October 1768. 
</p>
                        <p>Various cursive hands. Rough nastaʿlīq, taʿlīq, and shikastah āmīz. 
</p>
                        <p>Stamped and Persian foliation. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_317199908">Tāj al-Dīn ibn Muʿīn al-Dīn Malikī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_317199908">تاج الدّين ابن معين الدّين ملكى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
